# SE/30 A/UX 3.0.1 Boot (retail SE floppy).
#
# Proves that A/UX 3.0.1 successfully mounts its root filesystem from the
# retail Install CD-ROM.  The kernel routine vfs_mountroot() (at $10032BC2)
# panics via $10020454 on any failure ("no root file system", "rootmount
# cannot mount root", or VFS_ROOT error) and otherwise returns via RTS at
# $10032CFC after:
#   1. probe_root() found exactly one matching fs_types[] entry for the
#      CD-ROM's rootdev,
#   2. real_mount() returned 0 (successful mount),
#   3. VFS_ROOT() returned 0 (root vnode populated).

# 1) Set a breakpoint at the mount-success address.
break $10032CFC

# 2) Run enough instructions to reach and pass the success address.
#    Observed reach time is ~93M instructions; budget ~2.7x that to absorb
#    timing jitter without overrunning into the post-mount boot phase.
run 250000000

# 3) Assert that PC stopped exactly at the success address (and nowhere
#    else).  If the run halted elsewhere (panic, fault, reset loop, or
#    instruction budget exhausted) the assert fails and the script exits
#    with a non-zero status.
assert pc == $10032CFC

quit
# SE/30 A/UX 3.0.1 Boot (retail SE floppy).
#
# Proves that A/UX 3.0.1 successfully mounts its root filesystem from the
# retail Install CD-ROM.  The kernel routine vfs_mountroot() (at $10032BC2)
# panics via $10020454 on any failure ("no root file system", "rootmount
# cannot mount root", or VFS_ROOT error) and otherwise returns via RTS at
# $10032CFC after:
#   1. probe_root() found exactly one matching fs_types[] entry for the
#      CD-ROM's rootdev,
#   2. real_mount() returned 0 (successful mount),
#   3. VFS_ROOT() returned 0 (root vnode populated).
#
# The emulator deterministically stops at $10032CFC around ~93M
# instructions with D0=$00000000.  We capture the on-screen "Welcome to
# A/UX. Launching..." boot screen at that exact point and compare it to
# the reference PNG.  Any failure path (panic, reset loop, different stop
# address) produces a different screen and fails the match.

# Success breakpoint: vfs_mountroot RTS (only reached on full mount success).
break $10032CFC

# Panic breakpoint: kernel panic() entry (catches every failure mode).
break $10020454

# Budget ~2.7x observed reach time (~93M) so timing jitter cannot overrun
# into the post-mount phase, which would alter the "Launching..." screen.
run 250000000
info regs

# Assert: PC must be $10032CFC (mount success).  The reference image is
# pixel-identical across runs of this deterministic boot.
screenshot match mount-success.png

quit
